'''Dato Chan Tien Ghee''' ({{zh|s=曾长义|zh|t=曾長義|p=Zēng Cháng Yì}}), more commonly known as '''TG''', is a [[Malaysians|Malaysian]] businessman, who was the chairman of [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City Football Club]] from May 2010 to March 2013.<ref name=BBC21631486/>

==Cardiff City==
Chan Tien Ghee  became chairman on 27 May 2010. His aim was to get Cardiff into the [[Premier League]] and stated that [[Dave Jones (football manager)|Dave Jones]] would carry on being manager, whilst also hiring Gethin Jenkins from [[Dragons (rugby union)|Newport Gwent Dragons]] to become Chief Executive of the club.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/teams/c/cardiff_city/8783906.stm Cardiff chairman Datuk Chan Tien Ghee cools fan fears] from [[BBC News]]</ref> However, Cardiff failed to get promoted at the end of his first season as chairman. He resigned the position as chairman in March 2013, to pursue other business opportunities.<ref name=BBC21631486>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/21631486|title=Cardiff City chairman Dato Chan Tien Ghee resigns|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|date=1 March 2013|accessdate=1 March 2013}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Tien Ghee is the father of the Malaysian footballer that is currently playing for [[Kelantan FA]], Nicholas Chan.<ref>[http://www.cardiff.vitalfootball.co.uk/article.asp?a=199947 Cardiff City Set To Sign Nick Chan - Son of TG ?] Retrieved at January 11, 2011</ref>

