{{primary sources |date=April 2018}} {{Infobox magazine |title = Financial Mail |image_file = Financial Mail (October 2011 magazine cover).jpg |image_size = |image_caption= |editor = Rob Rose |frequency = Weekly |circulation = 18,386<ref>{{cite web|title=Advertise With Us|work=Financial Mail|accessdate=October 23, 2016|url=http://www.financialmail.co.za/advertise/}}</ref> |category = [[Newsmagazine]] |publisher = |firstdate = 1959 |Political = |alignmentcountry= |company = [[Times Media Group]] |based = [[Johannesburg]] |language = English |website = {{URL|http://www.fm.co.za}} |issn = }}
'''''Financial Mail''''' (or the '''''FM''''', as it is widely known), is a [[South Africa]]n business publication focused on reaching the country's top business people. This weekly publication, which was launched in 1959, underwent a major "look and feel" change in 2006, which saw it reclaim its position as the most widely read English business weekly in the country. The FM also publishes a series of popular corporate profiles as well as annual publications such as The Little Black Book, AdFocus and The Property Handbook.
